{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThreadPool"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A thread pool is useful when you wish to asynchronously fork out the execution of work"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and continue working in your own thread. If that will happen often, the overhead of starting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and destroying a thread each time might be too high. In such cases reusing already started","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads seems like a good idea. And it indeed is, but implementing this can be tedious","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and error-prone.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Therefore GLib provides thread pools for your convenience. An added advantage is, that the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads can be shared between the different subsystems of your program, when they are using GLib.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a new thread pool, you use [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.new"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is destroyed by [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.free","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to execute a certain task within a thread pool, use [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.push","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To get the current number of running threads you call [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To get the number of still unprocessed tasks you call [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.unprocessed"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"To control the maximum number of threads for a thread pool, you use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. and [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally you can control the number of unused threads, that are kept alive by GLib for future use."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The current number can be fetched with [func"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The maximum number can be controlled by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_unused_threads"},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_unused_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]. All currently unused threads"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be stopped by calling [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.stop_unused_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"ThreadPool","externalID":"s:4GLib10ThreadPoolC","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers